article.headline: VMI 103, Radford 94
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Reggie Williams scored 28 points, Chavis Holmes had 27 and VMI forced 41 turnovers as the Keydets defeated Radford 103-94 Thursday night. The Keydets (10-12, 3-3 Big South) used a 20-4 run that started with 8:56 remaining to put the game out of reach. The score had been tied nine times until that point. Travis Holmes added 24 for VMI and Matt Murrer scored 15. Chris Oliver scored 31 points for Radford (7-15, 2-5), Martell McDuffy and Reggie McIntyre had 17 each and the Highlanders outrebounded the Keydets 45-23. But VMI turned Radford's turnovers into 55 points. Oliver added 11 rebounds for the Highlanders.
